title: Something's Missing
lyrics:
I’ve seen you’re a beggar
In search of the sweetest wine
You found that fruit digging up roots
I heard it from a friend of mine

They tell me you’re a lender
Living on borrowed time
You’re speaking of proof with half a truth
You’re stealing that stack of dimes

Something’s missing, something’s wrong
C’mon people pass it on
Something’s missing, something’s wrong
Hallelujah sister sing along
Something’s missing, something’s wrong
If I could change this song
I’d move this train along

They tell me you are a scholar
The quiet one in the back
The papers on the wall don’t they say it all
You got nothing because you’re keeping track

Can’t you hear me oh wise man
Don’t you wanna be like me
Places we don’t go, things we ought not know
Nothing gonna set us free
Hey Mr. Speaker
Your tongue tied up in lies
Selling that crap that we’d take back
If only we could open our eyes

Something’s missing, something’s wrong
C’mon people pass it on
Something’s missing, something’s wrong
Hallelujah sing along
Something’s missing, something’s wrong
If I could change this song
I’d move this train along
